ruinis : according to Sidgwiok means the discharges or showers of matter thrown up. Page considers it to have a double meaning, being used both of the fall of the showers, and of the devastation caused by them. Conington points out that the word is occasionally used of violent motion. It is best to translate ruinis in its ordinary sense of ‘ downfall.‘ The poet probably intended the word to be quite vague, but to express chiefly the notion of falling masses oslava, &c.
